# Velveeta Cheese Sauce

> Great for dipping baked pretzels or pouring over a baked potato, this cheese sauce is just the right amount of “processed”. #side #app #ingredient

- Velveeta | 8 oz | Cubed
- Milk | 1/2 cup | 

In a saucepan, gently heat the milk over medium heat. Be careful not to let it boil.

Add the cubed Velveeta to the milk. Stir continuously until the cheese is completely melted and the mixture is smooth.

- Paprika | 1/4 teaspoon | 
- Garlic Powder | 1/4 teaspoon | 
- Salt | to taste | 
- Black Pepper | to taste | 

Stir in the paprika and garlic powder. Add salt and pepper to your taste.

If the sauce is too thick, add a little more milk to reach your desired consistency.

Enjoy your cheese sauce over vegetables, nachos, or your favorite pasta!
